ew)<br>&gt;*gets on hands and knees and makes antlers with hands on his head* look at me...I'm a MOOSE!!!<br><br>His girlfriend got asked....if you could send one thing to Japan in a box that would explain Canada what would you send<br>&gt;A Native American *jokingly*<br>Why? (not taking it as a joke)....<br><br>She eventually explained her way out of it...both were chosen and went to the same area....<br>So the interview might seem harsh...but you'll likely get in anyway....<br>Oh....And a hint....if it's not to late...you should try and get into tottori....it's a beautiful area (the big cities have too many people apply)....and you can go to chizu nourin high school....I have friends there....and there's lots of great looking girls....especially the one teacher....Morimatsu-sensei...I fell in love with her...Incredible looking (Better than incredible....more beautiful than japan)....smart...fun...Nice but a little shy....AND....She's an english teacher....and she looks about 1/2 her age...<br>Damn I miss everyone there... :-(<br>She's not the only one....<br> <p><pre>--%) Picasso Smilie---               Single Handedly saving the porn industry--I'm a little out of wack...If you happen to have any extra whack please contact me...Thank you--</pre></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ucyangoose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cyangoose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/8/02 11:47:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=645.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interviewing with JET</span><hr size=1> Hehe..I'm female, so, I'll ignore the cute females part.  Someone told me to brush up on politics before I interview too.  <br><br>Thanks. <p><a href=http://www.geocities.com/fsdrl>Nihongo o Narau: Learn Japanese</a><img src=http://learn-japanese.50megs.com/actionbadge.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/8/02 9:42:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=645.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interviewing with JET</span><hr size=1> Well...knowing politics and history is a bonus...basically you go and teach english and a bit about your country...(probably mostly from questions from curious kids)...<br>just be friendly and be yourself...even if you're not a politician you'll likely have something to offer...(like being decent with japanese language...most pick it up later)....you get most of what you need from the training and the stack of books that you get...<br><br>And for some reason I always imagined you were a guy...Hmm...go figure...I can't think of anything that would have swayed my opinion either way though....I guess you can't assume anything...<br> <p><pre>--%) Picasso Smilie---               Single Handedly saving the porn industry--I'm a little out of wack...If you happen to have any extra whack please contact me...Thank you--</pre></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=645.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=645.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=645.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimag